---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Terms and Conditions — PrivacyComply",
  "url": "https://privacycomply.io/terms.html",
  "publisher": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "PrivacyComply", "url": "https://privacycomply.io/"}
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms and Conditions — PrivacyComply"
  description="The terms that govern your use of PrivacyComply. Generated and maintained with iubenda."
  canonical="/terms.html"
  ogType="website"
  robots="index,follow"
>
  <Fragment slot="schema">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <article class="article">
    <header class="article-head">
      <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="article-lead">The terms that govern your access to and use of PrivacyComply. Maintained with iubenda so it stays current with Canadian and applicable international consumer-protection law.</p>
    </header>

    <p>Our authoritative, always-current terms and conditions are hosted by iubenda. Open the full document below.</p>

    <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <a href="https://www.iubenda.com/terms-and-conditions/54102151" class="iubenda-white iubenda-noiframe iubenda-embed btn btn-primary" title="Terms and Conditions">View our full Terms and Conditions</a>
    </p>
    <script is:inline type="text/javascript">
      (function (w,d) {
        var loader = function () {
          var s = d.createElement("script"), tag = d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];
          s.src = "https://cdn.iubenda.com/iubenda.js";
          tag.parentNode.insertBefore(s, tag);
        };
        if (w.addEventListener) { w.addEventListener("load", loader, false); }
        else if (w.attachEvent) { w.attachEvent("onload", loader); }
        else { w.onload = loader; }
      })(window, document);
    </script>

    <h2>Quick summary</h2>
    <p>The iubenda-hosted document is authoritative. Short version of what's in it:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>What PrivacyComply provides:</strong> Editorial reviews and informational guides about data-privacy compliance tools. Not legal advice.</li>
      <li><strong>Not a substitute for a lawyer:</strong> Nothing on this site constitutes legal advice. For specific legal questions about GDPR, CCPA, PIPEDA or any other regulation, consult a qualified attorney in your jurisdiction.</li>
      <li><strong>Affiliate relationships:</strong> Some links on the site are affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you sign up for a paid plan with a vendor we recommend. See our <a href="/about.html#disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for details.</li>
      <li><strong>No warranty:</strong> Reviews reflect our editorial judgment at time of publication. Vendors change pricing, features, and policies; we update when we can but you should verify current details on the vendor's own site before signing up.</li>
      <li><strong>Intellectual property:</strong> Site content is © PrivacyComply (Strandway Ventures) unless otherwise noted. Linking and short, attributed quotation are welcome.</li>
      <li><strong>Jurisdiction:</strong> These terms are governed by the laws of Nova Scotia, Canada.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Related</h2>
    <p>See also our <a href="/privacy-policy.html">Privacy Policy</a>, <a href="/cookie-policy.html">Cookie Policy</a>, and <a href="/about.html#disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.</p>

    <p style="margin-top: 3rem; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--c-muted, #666);">Last reviewed: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-CA', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long' })}. The iubenda-hosted terms linked above are updated automatically when our business model or relevant law changes.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
